[src:dependency-parsing-nlp/natural-language-processing] Also, given that words in the same language are spoken by people with different accents, the speech recognition software must be able to recognize the wide variety of input as being identical to each other in terms of its textual equivalent.
[src:dependency-parsing-nlp/natural-language-processing] Given a sound clip of a person or people speaking, separate it into words.
[src:dependency-parsing-nlp/natural-language-processing] Given a text, transform those units and produce a spoken representation.
[src:dependency-parsing-nlp/natural-language-processing] Text-to-speech can be used to aid the visually impaired.
[src:dependency-parsing-nlp/natural-language-processing] is a text-processing technique that divides text into individual words or word fragments.
[src:dependency-parsing-nlp/natural-language-processing] This technique results in two key components: a word index and tokenized text.
[src:dependency-parsing-nlp/natural-language-processing] The word index is a list that maps unique words to specific numerical identifiers, and the tokenized text replaces each word with its corresponding numerical token.
[src:dependency-parsing-nlp/natural-language-processing] These numerical tokens are then used in various deep learning methods.
